Baltimore Ravens Plan to Release McGahee, Mason and Heap, ESPN Reports

-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 
2011-07-26T04:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-26/baltimore-ravens-plan-to-release-mcgahee-mason-and-heap-espn-reports.html
The  Baltimore Ravens  will cut
running back Willis McGahee, wide receiver Derrick Mason and
tight end Todd Heap this week,  ESPN reported .  With the National Football League lockout over, teams will
be able to release players on July 28.  McGahee, 29, rushed for 300 yards in 15 games for the
Ravens last season while sharing time with starting running back
Ray Rice. Mason, 37, had 61 receptions for 802 yards and seven
touchdowns for Baltimore last season, while Heap, 31, had 40
catches for 599 yards and five scores.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Erik Matuszewski in New York at 
 matuszewski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at   msillup@bloomberg.net  